replies.body:
@Willis Dogg

As i mentioned in my 3rd post directed towards Raldrid, this system is aiming to support the players WITH a disconnect on their team, rather than the focus being on the disconnected player. I'm sure Riot would happily revert the LP loss if they were 100% certain it was their fault and you could prove it, however you cant because there are so many variables that cause an error and so many people can lie in order to not be punished.  

If you have a cheap / bad graphics card and crash often, your team mates shouldn't be punished. I also previously mentioned, if this system loses you a lot of LP, look towards a solution because obviously it's related to you (in this case, your graphics card) and not Riot.

@Warmazzta Well put :-)

@LeagueTrashGame

The client does crash and that is unfortunate, and they shouldn't be punished for it in a perfect world because stuff like that does happen. 

However, Many people would begin to quit intentionally if the system >DIDNT< punish those who didn't connect, if you have some person you hate on your team or you are against a counter pick, what would stop you from never connecting if you weren't going to be punished for it?

It doesn't occur now because they will be punished by having an LP loss and a queue timer for never connecting, all this system will do is make it so the 4 others >wont< be punished whereas in the current state of the game, the 4 remaining players are still being punished for having an AFK on their team.
